@ArturNiederfahrenhorst @sven1977 I have a nit about this pattern that I am seeing a lot throughout RLlib's codebase.
I think we should treat config as a "const" obj. This is what users tell us, and likely what we should record with our checkpoints etc. modifying this in-place feels pretty confusing.
if we need to derive a control bit from some user configured inputs, we can create an internal only local configuration, but that should be part of the implementation details, not getting reflected back at the original cfg.

