An alternative way to implement this `latest weights` feature could be to maintain `pretrained=True` as a shortcut to get always the most updated weights. This USED to be the case since all models had only a single weight. There were even cases where old weights moved to `pretrained="legacy"` (see [here](https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/main/torchvision/models/detection/keypoint_rcnn.py#L379-L380)). So in a sense one could argue that the default behaviour of `pretrained=True` is currently to return the best available weights, hence it's not BC-breaking. Note that this approach is followed by other libraries where they overwrite directly the weights in-place.

Doing this will get us automatic adoption to the best/greatest weights while at the same time it will allow users who want to always access specific weights to be able to do so. Thoughts?

